A man believed to be in his 40s was found dead inside his car riddled with bullet holes on the M7 in the Rossburgh area, south of Durban, on Tuesday. Spokesperson for Emer-G-Med, Kyle van Reenen, said they found a grey Volkswagen polo peppered with bullet holes. He said the man was found seated in the driver's seat with multiple gunshot wounds. “He was declared dead on arrival of paramedics. A passenger was found to have suffered moderate injuries and was treated and stabilised on scene before being taken to a nearby hospital for further care,” said van Reenen. Police were at the scene and are investigating.